## Install

```bash
npm install --save {{packageName}}
```

## Usage

[{{{packageName}}}][] is built into [@yozora/parser][]{{#if inGfmEx}}, [@yozora/parser-gfm-ex][]{{/if}}{{#if inGfm}}, and [@yozora/parser-gfm][]{{/if}}.

### With `DefaultParser`

A tokenizer must be registered with an `IParser` before use.

```typescript{{#unless isFallbackTokenizer}} {4,9}{{/unless}}
import { DefaultParser } from '@yozora/core-parser'
import ParagraphTokenizer from '@yozora/tokenizer-paragraph'
import TextTokenizer from '@yozora/tokenizer-text'
{{#unless isFallbackTokenizer}}
import {{{toPascalCase tokenizerName}}}Tokenizer from '{{{packageName}}}'
{{/unless}}

const parser = new DefaultParser()
  .useFallbackTokenizer(new ParagraphTokenizer())
  .useFallbackTokenizer(new TextTokenizer())
{{#unless isFallbackTokenizer}}
  .useTokenizer(new {{{toPascalCase tokenizerName}}}Tokenizer())
{{/unless}}

parser.parse({{{usageDemoSourceContent}}})
```

### With [@yozora/parser][]

```typescript
import YozoraParser from '@yozora/parser'

const parser = new YozoraParser()
parser.parse({{{usageDemoSourceContent}}})
```

